la]]\n**[[Giarmata]]\n**[[Giera]]\n**[[Giroc]]\n**[[Giulv\u0103z]]\n**[[Gottlob, Timi\u0219|Gottlob]]\n**[[Iecea Mare]]\n**[[Jamu Mare]]\n**[[Jebel, Timi\u0219|Jebel]]\n**[[Lenauheim]]\n**[[Liebling, Timi\u0219|Liebling]]\n**[[Livezile, Timi\u0219|Livezile]]\n**[[Lovrin]]\n**[[Margina]]\n**[[Ma\u0219loc]]\n**[[M\u0103n\u0103\u0219tiur]]\n**[[Moravi\u021ba]]\n**[[Mo\u0219ni\u021ba Nou\u0103]]\n**[[N\u0103drag]]\n**[[Ni\u021bchidorf]]\n**[[Ohaba Lung\u0103]]\n**[[Or\u021bi\u0219oara]]\n**[[Otelec]]\n**[[Par\u021ba]]\n**[[P\u0103dureni, Timi\u0219|P\u0103dureni]]\n**[[Peciu Nou]]\n**[[Periam]]\n**[[Pesac]]\n**[[Pietroasa, Timi\u0219|Pietroasa]]\n**[[Pi\u0219chia]]\n**[[Racovi\u021ba, Timi\u0219|Racovi\u021ba]]\n**[[Remetea Mare]]\n**[[Saco\u0219u Turcesc]]\n**[[Saravale]]\n**[[Satchinez]]\n**[[S\u0103c\u0103laz]]\n**[[S\u00e2nandrei]]\n**[[S\u00e2nmihaiu Rom\u00e2n]]\n**[[S\u00e2npetru Mare]]\n**[[Seca\u0219]]\n**[[\u0218ag]]\n**[[\u0218andra]]\n**[[\u0218tiuca]]\n**[[Teremia Mare]]\n**[[Tome\u0219ti, Timi\u0219|Tome\u0219ti]]\n**[[Tomnatic]]\n**[[Topolov\u0103\u021bu Mare]]\n**[[Tormac]]\n**[[Traian Vuia, Timi\u0219|Traian Vuia]]\n**[[Uivar]]\n**[[Varia\u0219]]\n**[[V\u0103lcani]]\n**[[Victor Vlad Delamarina, Timi\u0219|Victor Vlad Delamarina]]\n**[[Voiteg]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Lion and Sun#Other (non-Iranian) variants|Lion and Sun]]\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Timi\u0219 County}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\nGoogle earth file (kmz) with information about the Timis Bega catchment and the 2005 flood event [https://docs.google.com/leaf?id=0B8rexSnYSYCjOTY1NGYwMzItZWM5MS00YzkyLWI2NjctODI1YTEyMGJjYWI2&hl=en Download the kmz file]\n\n{{Timi\u0219 County}}\n{{Counties (judete) of Romania}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Timis County}}\n[[Category:Timi\u0219 County| ]]\n[[Category:Counties of Romania]]\n[[Category:1968 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1968]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|County of Romania}}\n{{distinguish|Temes County}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Expand Romanian|Jude\u021bul Timi\u0219|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Timi\u0219 County\n| native_name                     = Jude\u021bul Timi\u0219\n| settlement_type                 = County\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_link                       = \n| image_shield                    = Timis county coat of arms.png\n| shield_link                     = \n| image_map                       = Timis in Romania.svg\n| map_caption                     = Timi\u0219 county, territorial location\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{ROU}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Development regions of Romania|Development region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Vest (development region)|Vest]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Historical regions of Romania|Historical region]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Banat]]\n| subdivision_type3               = County seat\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Timi\u0219oara]]\n| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = County Council\n| leader_party                    = [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|PSD]]\n| leader_title                    = President of the County Council\n| leader_name                     = C\u0103lin Dobra\n| leader_title1                   = Prefect\n| leader_name1                    = Eugen Dogariu <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prefecturatimis.ro/prezentare.php?nivel=3|title=Institutia Prefectului judetul Timis|first=Werbo|last=office@werbo.ro|website=www.prefecturatimis.ro}}</ref>\n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = 8,697\n| area_rank                       = [[List of Romanian counties by area|1st]]\n| area_land_km2                   = \n| area_water_km2                  = \n| area_total_sq_mi                = \n| area_land_sq_mi                 = \n| area_water_sq_mi                = \n| area_water_percent              = \n| area_urban_km2                  = \n| area_urban_sq_mi                = \n| area_metro_km2                  = \n| area_metro_sq_mi                = \n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|45.78|21.35|display=inline}}\n| population_as_of                = 2011 census<ref name=\"INSSER\">{{cite web|url=http://www.recensamantromania.ro/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sR_TAB_3.xlsx |title=Population at 20 October 2011 |date=5 July 2013 |accessdate=9 July 2013 |publisher=[[National Institute of Statistics (Romania)|INSSE]] |language=Romanian |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_total                = 683,540 {{increase}}\n| population_rank                 = [[List of Romanian counties by population|6th]]\n| population_density_km2          = 78\n| population_density_sq_mi        = \n| population_metro                = \n| population_density_metro_km2    = \n| population_density_metro_sq_mi  = \n| population_urban                = \n| population_density_urban_km2    = \n| population_density_urban_sq_mi  = \n| population_note                 = \n| timezone                        = [[Eastern European Time|EET]]\n| utc_offset                      = +2\n| timezone_DST                    = [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST                  = +3\n| postal_code_type                = [[List of postal codes in Romania|Postal Code]]\n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = (+40) 256 or (+40) 356\n| blank_name                      = [[Romanian car number plates|Car Plates]]\n| blank_info                      = TM\n| footnotes                       = \n| website                         = [http://www.cjtimis.ro/ County Council]<br />[http://www.prefecturatimis.ro/ County Prefecture]\n| telpref                         = 56\n| iso_code                        = RO-TM\n| official_name                   = \n| blank1_name                     = GDP (nominal)\n| blank1_info                     = US$ 11.230&nbsp;billion (''2018'') {{increase}}\n| blank2_name                     = GDP/[[capita]]\n| blank2_info                     = US$ 16,430 (''2018''){{increase}}\n| blank3_name                     = Economy rank\n| blank3_info                     = [[List of Romanian counties by GDP|2nd]]\n}}\n\n'''Timi\u0219''' ({{IPA-ro|\u02c8timi\u0283}}) is a county ([[jude\u021b]]) of western [[Romania]] on the border with [[Hungary]] and [[Serbia]], in the historical region [[Banat]], with the county seat at [[Timi\u0219oara]]. It is the westernmost and the largest county in Romania in terms of land area. The county is also part of the [[Danube\u2013Cri\u0219\u2013Mure\u0219\u2013Tisa Euroregion]].\n\n==Name==\nThe name of the county comes from the river [[Timi\u0219 (river)|Timi\u0219]], known in Roman antiquity as river {{lang|la|Tibisis}} or {{lang|la|Tibiscus}}.\n\nIn [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]], it is known as ''Temes megye'', [[German language|German]] as ''Kreis Temesch'', in [[Serbian language|Serbian]] as \u0422\u0430\u043c\u0438\u0448 / ''Tami\u0161'', in [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] as \u0422\u0456\u0301\u043c\u0456\u0448, and in [[Banat Bulgarian dialect|Banat Bulgarian]] as {{lang|bg-Latn|Timi\u0161}}.\n\n==Demographics==\nIn 2000, the county had a population of 684,506 and the [[population density]] was 79/km\u00b2. According to the 2011 census, the county had a population of 683,540 and the [[population density]] was 78/km\u00b2. The reported ethnic groups were as follows:<ref>National Institute of Statistics, ''[http://www.recensamant.ro/pagini/tabele/t40a.pdf \"Popula\u021bia dup\u0103 etnie\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090816034908/http://www.recensamant.ro/pagini/tabele/t40a.pdf |date=2009-08-16 }}''</ref>\n\n*[[Romanians]] - 85.52%\n*[[Hungarians]] - 5.43%\n*[[Roma in Romania|Roma]] - 2.23%\n*[[Germans]] <small>([[Banat Swabians]])</small> - 1.3%\n*[[Serbs]] - 2%\n*[[Ukrainians]] - 0.91%\n*[[Bulgarians]] - 0.8%\n*Others - 0.7%\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! County population<ref>National Institute of Statistics, ''[http://www.insse.ro/rpl2002rezgen/18.pdf \"Popula\u021bia la recens\u0103mintele din anii 1948, 1956, 1966, 1977, 1992 \u0219i 2002\"]''</ref>\n|-\n| 1948\n| 588,936\n|-\n| 1956\n|{{decrease}} 568,881\n|-\n| 1966\n|{{increase}} 607,596\n|-\n| 1977\n|{{increase}} 696,884\n|-\n| 1992\n|{{increase}} 700,292\n|-\n| 2002\n|{{decrease}} 677,926\n|-\n| 2011\n|{{increase}} 683,540\n|}\n\n==Geography==\nThis county has a total area of 8,697&nbsp;km\u00b2 (3,6% of Romania). It is the largest county in Romania.\n\nIn the eastern extremity are the [[Poiana Rusc\u0103 Mountains]] from the [[Western Romanian Carpathians]] group. Elevations decrease to the west, passing through the [[Lipova Hills]] to the [[Western Romanian Plain]], the eastern part of the [[Pannonian Plain]].\n\nThe county is crossed by many rivers, the most important being the [[Bega (Tisza)|Bega]] and the [[Timi\u0219 (river)|Timi\u0219]].\n\n===Neighbours===\n{{Romanian counties map|width=250px}}\n* [[Hunedoara County]] to the east.\n* [[Hungary]] to the northwest - [[Csongr\u00e1d (county)|Csongr\u00e1d County]].\n* [[Arad County]] to the north.\n* [[Cara\u0219-Severin County]] to the south.\n* [[Serbia]] to the southwest - [[Vojvodina]] [[Autonomous Province]] - [[North Banat District]] and [[Central Banat District]].\n\n==Economy==\nTimi\u0219 County has one of the most dynamic economies in [[Romania]], being a region with among the highest ratings of foreign investment due to its tradition and its position.\n\nThe predominant industries in the county are:\n* Mechanical manufacturing\n* Food\n* Chemicals\n* [[Textiles]]\n* [[Electronic components]]\n* Wood\n\n==Tourism==\nThe main tourist attractions in the county are:\n* [[Timi\u0219oara]]\n* [[Lugoj]]\n* [[Buzia\u0219]] Resort.\n* Castles at [[Banloc]] and [[Carani]].\n* The area around [[F\u0103get]].\n\nThere are also a lot of places for hunting and fishing.\n\n==Politics==\nThe Timi\u0219 County Council, elected at the [[2016 Romanian local election|2016 local government elections]], is made up of 37 counselors, with the following party composition:<ref name=\"LocalElections2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.2016bec.ro/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/SIAL2016_CJ_mandate.xlsx|title=Mandate de CJ pe judete si competitori|publisher=Biroul Electoral Central|date=10 June 2016|accessdate=16 June 2016|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n{| cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | Party\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" | Seats\n! style=\"background:#ccc\" colspan=\"16\" | Current County Council\n|-\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| [[Social Democratic Party (Romania)|Social Democratic Party]]\n| style=\"text-align: right\" | '''16'''\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD}} | &nbsp;\n| {{Romanian politics/party colours/PSD