share.cfm?SHARESHED=2159 Huts]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081109070803/http://savingbletchleypark.org/ Saving Bletchley Park] blog by [[Sue Black (computer scientist)|Sue Black]]\n* {{YouTube|fKQYECYJEH0|19 minute Video interview}} with [[Sue Black (computer scientist)|Sue Black]] by [[Robert Llewellyn]] about Bletchley Park\n* {{citation |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/history/world-war-two/9765962/Bletchleys-forgotten-heroes.html |title=Bletchley's forgotten heroes |first=Ian |last=Douglas |work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |date=25 December 2012}}\n* [http://bobmeades-ivil.tripod.com/id13.html C4 Station X 1999 on DVD here]\n* [http://www.iwm.org.uk/history/how-alan-turing-cracked-the-enigma-code How Alan Turing Cracked The Enigma Code] Imperial War Museums\n* [https://audioboom.com/channel/bletchley-park The Bletchley Park Podcast] on Audioboom\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cryptography organizations]]\n[[Category:Milton Keynes]]\n[[Category:Locations in the history of espionage]]\n[[Category:Country houses in Buckinghamshire]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Buckinghamshire]]\n[[Category:World War II sites in England]]\n[[Category:Museums in Buckinghamshire]]\n[[Category:Bletchley Park| ]]\n[[Category:British Telecom buildings and structures]]\n[[Category:Military and war museums in England]]\n[[Category:Historic house museums in Buckinghamshire]]\n[[Category:Toy museums in England]]\n[[Category:Biographical museums in Buckinghamshire]]\n[[Category:Signals intelligence of World War II]]\n[[Category:History museums in Buckinghamshire]]\n[[Category:World War II museums in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Telecommunications museums in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Museums established in 1993]]\n[[Category:1993 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Foreign Office during World War II]]\n", "name_user": "TedColes", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bletchley_Park"}
{"title_page": "Gunung Putri railway station", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Gunung Putri Station\n| native_name         = <small>Stasiun Gunung Putri</small>\n| native_name_lang    = \n| image               = Vandalism in Gunung Putri Station (2015).jpg\n| image_caption       = The station is full of vandalism\n| address             = Jl. Raya Mayor Oking, [[Gunung Putri]], [[Bogor Regency]] 16961\n| borough = [[West Java]]\n| country             = [[Indonesia]]\n| coordinates         = {{coord|-6.4719|106.8887|type:railwaystation_region:ID|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation           = +115M\n| line                = {{ubl|\n|{{rint|jakarta|yellow}} [[KA Commuter Line Jatinegara-Bogor|Yellow Line]]\n}}\n| other               =\n| platform            = 1 side platform\n| tracks              = 1\n| parking             = \n| bicycle             = Available\n| baggage_check       =\n| passengers          =\n| pass_year           =\n| pass_percent        =\n| pass_system         =\n| opened              =1997\n| opening = \n| status = Not in service\n| electrified = 2012\n| closed              =2006\n| rebuilt             =\n| ADA                 = Available\n| code                = GPI\n| owned               = [[PT Kereta Api Indonesia]]\n| operator            = [[KA Commuter Jabodetabek]]\n| zone                =\n| services            = {{s-rail|title=KRL Jabodetabek}}\n{{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Nambo-Angke|previous=Nambo|next=Cibinong|rows1=2}}\n{{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Nambo-Depok|previous=Nambo|next=Cibinong|hide1=yes}}\n{{s-note|text=Connections}}\n{{rail line\n|previous=[[Cibinong railway station|Cibinong]]\n|route=[[Citayam\u2013Nambo railway]]\n|next=[[Nambo railway station|Nambo]]}}\n| map_type            = Indonesia_Bogor Regency\n| map_caption         = Location in [[Bogor Regency]]\n}}\n'''Gunung Putri Station''' is an Indonesian train station located in [[Gunung Putri]], [[Bogor Regency|Bogor]]. The station is located at an elevation of +115 m. It is included in the Jakarta Operation Area I.\n\nAlthough not servicing passengers, there is a market located right above the station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.re-digest.web.id/2015/12/mengunjungi-pasar-jumat-pagi-stasiun.html?m=1|title=Mengunjungi Pasar Jumat Pagi Stasiun Gunung Putri|language=id|first=|last=|publisher=Bayu Tri Sulistyo}}</ref> It opens on Friday.\n\n==Schedule==\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Bogor Regency]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in West Java]]\n\n{{KCJ Angke - Nambo Line}}\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|West Java}}\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Gunung Putri Station\n| native_name         = <small>Stasiun Gunung Putri</small>\n| native_name_lang    = \n| image               = Vandalism in Gunung Putri Station (2015).jpg\n| image_caption       = The station is full of vandalism\n| address             = Jl. Raya Mayor Oking, [[Gunung Putri]], [[Bogor Regency]] 16961\n| borough = [[West Java]]\n| country             = [[Indonesia]]\n| coordinates         = {{coord|-6.4719|106.8887|type:railwaystation_region:ID|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation           = +115M\n| line                = {{ubl|\n|{{rint|jakarta|yellow}} [[KA Commuter Line Jatinegara-Bogor|Yellow Line]]\n}}\n| other               =\n| platform            = 1 side platform\n| tracks              = 1\n| parking             = \n| bicycle             = Available\n| baggage_check       =\n| passengers          =\n| pass_year           =\n| pass_percent        =\n| pass_system         =\n| opened              =1997\n| opening = \n| status = Not in service\n| electrified = 2012\n| closed              =2006\n| rebuilt             =\n| ADA                 = Available\n| code                = GPI\n| owned               = [[PT Kereta Api Indonesia]]\n| operator            = [[KA Commuter Jabodetabek]]\n| zone                =\n| services            = {{s-rail|title=KRL Jabodetabek}}\n{{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Nambo-Angke|previous=Nambo|next=Cibinong|rows1=2}}\n{{s-line|system=KRL Jabodetabek|line=Nambo-Depok|previous=Nambo|next=Cibinong|hide1=yes}}\n{{s-note|text=Connections}}\n{{rail line\n|previous=[[Cibinong railway station|Cibinong]]\n|route=[[Citayam\u2013Nambo railway]]\n|next=[[Nambo railway station|Nambo]]}}\n| map_type            = Indonesia_Bogor Regency\n| map_caption         = Location in [[Bogor Regency]]\n}}\n'''Gunung Putri Station''' is an Indonesian train station located in [[Gunung Putri]], [[Bogor Regency|Bogor]]. The station is located at an elevation of +115 m. It is included in the Jakarta Operation Area I.\n\nAlthough not servicing passengers, there is a market located right above the station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.re-digest.web.id/2015/12/mengunjungi-pasar-jumat-pagi-stasiun.html?m=1|title=Mengunjungi Pasar Jumat Pagi Stasiun Gunung Putri|language=id|first=|last=|publisher=Bayu Tri Sulistyo}}</ref> It opens on Friday.\n\n==Schedule==\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in West Java]]\n\n{{KCJ Angke - Nambo Line}}\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|West Java}}\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "name_user": "OktaRama2010", "label": "safe", "comment": "addedCategory:Bogor RegencyusingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gunung_Putri_railway_station"}
{"title_page": "YHLQMDLG", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = YHLQMDLG\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Bad Bunny]]\n| cover        = Bad Bunny - Yhlqmdlg.png\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{start date|2020|2|28|mf=y}}\n| recorded     = \n| studio       = \n| genre        =\n* [[Reggaeton]]\n* [[Latin trap]]\n* [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n| length       = 65:48\n| language     = \n| label        = Rimas\n| producer     =\n* Albert Hype\n* [[Bad Bunny]]\n* Based1\n* [[Chris Jeday]]\n* Demy & Clipz\n* Dez Wright\n* D\u00edmelo Flow\n* DJ Orma\n* Elikai\n* EMG\n* EZ Made da Beat\n* Frank King\n* Forthenight\n* Gaby Music\n* Haze\n* Hazen\n* Hide Miyabi\n* Jota Rosa\n* Lennex\n* Mora\n* Mvsis\n* [[Nesty (producer)|Nesty]]\n* Nino\n* Payday\n* Prida\n* Soteldo Beats\n* Subelo NEO\n* Taiko\n* [[Tainy]]\n* The Skybeats\n| prev_title   = [[Oasis (J Balvin and Bad Bunny album)|Oasis]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = YHLQMDLG\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Vete]]\n | single1date = November 22, 2019\n | single2     = Ignorantes\n | single2date = February 14, 2020\n | single3     = [[La Dif\u00edcil]]\n | single3date = February 29, 2020\n | single4     = Yo Perreo Sola<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/bad-bunny-drag-transformation-yo-perreo-sola-video-974467/|title=Bad Bunny Gets a Full Drag Makeover in New 'Yo Perreo Sola' Video|last=Exposito|first=Suzy|last2=Exposito|first2=Suzy|date=2020-03-27|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n | single4date = March 27, 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''YHLQMDLG''''' (abbreviation of \"Yo hago lo que me da la gana\", Spanish for \"I Do Whatever I Want\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/bad-bunny-drops-new-album-yhlqmdlg-listen/|title=Bad Bunny Drops New Album ''YHLQMDLG'': Listen|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Bloom|first=Madison|date=February 29, 2020|accessdate=March 1, 2020}}</ref>) is the second solo studio album (third overall) by Puerto Rican rapper and singer [[Bad Bunny]]. It was released on February 28, 2020, by Rimas Entertainment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/02/bad-bunny-i-do-what-i-want-album-announcement-release-date-cover-art|title=Bad Bunny Reveals Title, Release Date, and Cover Art for New Album|last=Espinoza|first=Joshua|website=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/bad-bunny-album-out-at-midnight-cover-art-title-reveal.html|title=Don't Freak Out, But Bad Bunny's New Album Drops at Midnight|last=Haylock|first=Zoe|website=[[Vulture (magazine)|Vulture]]|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2020/02/28/bad-bunny-yhlqmdlg-album-release-date|title=Bad Bunny to release new album YHLQMDLG this weekend|last=Renshaw|first=David|website=[[The Fader]]|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> It features guest appearances from [[Daddy Yankee]], Nesi, Yaviah, [[\u00d1engo Flow]], [[Sech (singer)|Sech]], Mora, [[Jowell & Randy]], [[Anuel AA]], [[Myke Towers]], [[Kendo Kaponi]], [[Arc\u00e1ngel (singer)|Arcangel]], [[Duki (rapper)|Duki]] and Pablo Chill-E. The album debuted at number two on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], becoming the highest-charting all-Spanish album ever on the chart.\n\n==Background and singles==\n\"[[Vete]]\" was released as the lead single of the album on November 22, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/11/bad-bunny-vete-music-video.html|title=Bad Bunny's Video for His New Breakup Song \"Vete\" Is a Series of Bad Bunny\u2013Level Flexes|last=Curto|first=Justin|website=Vulture|date=November 21, 2019|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> The album title was first mentioned during a sequence of the accompanying music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://talentomusical.net/confirmado-el-nuevo-album-de-bad-bunny-yhlqmdlg|title=Confirmado el nuevo \u00e1lbum de Bad Bunny ''YHLQMDLG''|last=Alvelo|first=Joel|website=talentomusical.net|language=es|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8548839/que-tire-pa-lante-continues-dominate-latin-charts-daddy-yankee|title=Daddy Yankee's \"Que Tire Pa Lante\" Continues Its Latin Charts Domination|last=Bustios|first=Pamela|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> The second single \"Ignorantes\" with Panamanian singer [[Sech (singer)|Sech]] came out on February 14, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/cmalone/2020/02/14/bad-bunny-previews-upcoming-album-with-sech-collab-ignorantes/|title=Bad Bunny Previews Upcoming Album With Sech Collab|last=Malone|first=Chris|website=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]|date=February 14, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref> Bad Bunny announced the album on February 27, 2020, during an appearance on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'' and stated that it would be released on [[Leap Day|Leap Day 2020]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/bad-bunny-announces-new-album-and-performs-on-fallon-watch/|title=Bad Bunny Announces New Album and Performs on Fallon: Watch|last=Hussey|first=Allison|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| MC = 88/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/yhlqmdlg/bad-bunny|title=YHLQMDLG by Bad Bunny, Reviews and Tracks|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=March 27, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[AllMusic]]''\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web |last1=Jurek |first1=Thom |title=YHLQMDLG - Bad Bunny - Songs, Reviews, Credits |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/yhlqmdlg-mw0003364590?1585282732518 |website=AllMusic |accessdate=27 March 2020 |language=en-us}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Consequence of Sound]]''\n| rev2score = B+<ref name=\"cof\">{{cite web |last1=Viila |first1=Lucas |title=Album Review: Bad Bunny Does What He Wants on the Sprawling YHLQMDLG |url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/03/album-review-bad-bunny-yhlqmdlg/ |website=Consequence of Sound |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev3score = 8.5/10<ref name=\"pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/bad-bunny-yhlqmdlg/|title=Bad Bunny: YHLQMDLG|first=Matthew|last=Ismael|date=March 5, 2020|accessdate=March 5, 2020|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev4score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"rstone\">{{cite web |last1=Exposito |first1=Suzy |title=Bad Bunny Demands the World Crossover to Him on 'YHLQMDLG' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/bad-bunny-yhlqmdlg-960729/ |website=Rolling Stone |accessdate=5 March 2020 |date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\nAt [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[Standard score|normalised]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album has an average score of 88 based on 5 reviews, indicating \"universal acclaim\".<ref name = \"MC\"/>\n\nWriting for ''[[AllMusic]]'', Thom Jurek stated Bad Bunny \"turns the notion of the cohesive urbano statement into a sprawling 20-track mix of styles, production techniques, and completely accessible hooks in a work of peerless musical invention,\" and described ''YHLQMDLG'' as \"a transformative fever dream of an album that accents freedom by breaking all the rules without writing new ones.\"<ref name=\"allmusic\"/> In ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', Suzy Exposito gave ''YHLQMDLG'' 4.5 stars, writing that Bad Bunny \"convenes a family reunion of his favorite rappers and reggaetoneros to produce a genre-promiscuous work of reggaeton a la marquesina.\"<ref name=\"rstone\" /> For ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'', Lucas Villa wrote that Bad Bunny \"is emerging as a rarity in the game like the mythical [[Mew (Pok\u00e9mon)|Mew]]. Benito is game-sharking a system that was once othering Latin music artists with his [[Sandungueo|perreo]] takeover of pop.\"<ref name=\"cof\"/> Matthew Ismael Ruiz in ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' deemed the album \"outstanding\" and described it as \"a big party record that pushes boundaries and pays homage to reggaet\u00f3n's past and future, all made by a swaggering star with absolutely nothing to prove.\"<ref name=\"pitchfork\"/>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''YHLQMDLG'' debuted at number two on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] dated March 14, 2020, earning 179,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, including 35,000 pure album sales in its first week. It earned  201.4 million on-demand streams in the country, achieving the biggest streaming week ever for a Latin album, surpassing the record set by [[Ozuna (singer)|Ozuna]]'s ''[[Aura (Ozuna album)|Aura]]'' (2018, 53.2 million streams). It is Bad Bunny's highest-charting album, and the highest-charting all-Spanish album to ever appear on the chart. Previous record-holders for an all-Spanish-language albums were [[Shakira]]'s ''[[Fijaci\u00f3n Oral, Vol. 1]]'' (2005) and [[Man\u00e1]]'s ''[[Amar es Combatir]]'' (2006), both at number four, while two mostly-Spanish albums have reached number one, [[Selena]]'s ''[[Dreaming of You (Selena album)|Dreaming of You]]'' (1995) and [[Il Divo]]'s ''[[Ancora]]'' (2006).<ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9330424/lil-baby-first-no-1-album|title=Lil Baby Earns First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'My Turn'|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=March 8, 2020|accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBad Bunny charted all 20 album tracks on the US [[Hot Latin Songs]] ranking dated March 14, setting several records: most concurrently charting titles in the top 10 (8), in the top 20 (18) and in the top 25 (20). With eight top 10 songs on the chart, Bad Bunny outdid himself as he previously held the record for the most simultaneous top 10s, with six (September 2019). With 18 songs in the top 20, he surpassed [[J Balvin]]'s nine-song mark (February 2020). Only Ozuna has placed more songs simultaneously on the chart, with 21 (September 2018). Bad Bunny brought his total career entries on the chart to a record 83, surpassing [[Daddy Yankee]]'s 74 entries.<ref name=\"BBLatin\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/9332997/bad-bunnys-entire-yhlqmdlg-album-is-on-the-hot-latin-songs-chart|title=Bad Bunny's Entire 'YHLQMDLG' Album Is on the Hot Latin Songs Chart|work=Billboard|last=Bustios|first=Pamela|date=March 11, 2020|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBad Bunny also placed 11 album tracks simultaneously on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], the most for any Latin artist performing only in Spanish.<ref name=\"BBLatin\"/>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll tracks were written by [[Bad Bunny|Benito Mart\u00ednez]], except where noted. Credits adapted from [[Universal Music Publishing Group]]'s catalog.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.umusicpub.com/us/Digital-Music-Library/album/98348/yhlqmdlg|title=Album Details: YHLQMDLG By Bad Bunny|website=[[Universal Music Publishing Group]]|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{track listing\n| writing_credits = yes\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| total_length = 65:48\n\n| title1 = Si Veo a Tu Mam\u00e1\n| extra1 = {{hlist|Subelo NEO|Elikai}}\n| length1 = 2:50\n\n| title2 = [[La Dif\u00edcil]]\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|Gabriel Mora|Jose Cruz|Freddy Montalvo|Jesus Prato}}\n| extra2 = {{hlist|Subelo NEO|Lennex|Mora}}\n| length2 = 2:43\n\n| title3 = Pero Ya No\n| writer3 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|Cruz|Montalvo|Dylan Cleary-Krell|Emanuel Gonzalez}}\n| extra3 = {{hlist|Subelo NEO|EMG|Dez Wright}}\n| length3 = 2:40\n\n| title4 = La Santa\n| note