|EZ Made da Beat|Prida|Subelo NEO}}\n| length12 = 2:55\n\n| title13 = Una Vez\n| note13 = featuring Mora\n| writer13 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|Mora|Cruz|Montalvo|Nicolas Jana}}\n| extra13 = Taiko\n| length13 = 3:52\n\n| title14 = Safaera\n| note14 = featuring [[Jowell & Randy]] and \u00d1engo Flow\n| extra14 = {{hlist|Tainy|DJ Orma}}\n| length14 = 4:55\n\n| title15 = 25/8\n| writer15 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|Cruz|Montalvo|Kaled Rivera|Ben Sturdivant|Felix Rodriguez|Jason Garcia}}\n| extra15 = {{hlist|Subelo NEO|Hide Miyabi|Based1|Elikai}}\n| length15 = 4:03\n\n| title16 = Est\u00e1 Cabr\u00f3n Ser Yo\n| note16 = featuring [[Anuel AA]]\n| writer16 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|[[Anuel AA|Emmanuel Gazmey]]|Frank Packer|Harald Sorebo}}\n| extra16 = {{hlist|Payday|Frank King}}\n| length16 = 3:47\n\n| title17 = Puesto Pa' Guerrial\n| note17 = featuring [[Myke Towers]]\n| writer17 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|I. Ortiz|Cruz|Montalvo|[[Myke Towers|Michael Torres]]}}\n| extra17 = {{hlist|Subelo NEO|Hazen}}\n| length17 = 3:10\n\n| title18 = P FKN R\n| note18 = featuring [[Kendo Kaponi]] and [[Arc\u00e1ngel]]\n| writer18 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|Charles Ocansey|Frederik Thrane|[[Kendo Kaponi|Jose Rivera]]|[[Arc\u00e1ngel|Austin Santos]]}}\n| extra18 = {{hlist|The Skybeats|Forthenight}}\n| length18 = 4:18\n\n| title19 = Hablamos Ma\u00f1ana\n| note19 = featuring [[Duki (rapper)|Duki]] and Pablo Chill-E\n| writer19 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|Marco Masis|Pablo Acevedo|Mauro Lombardo|Carlos Melendez}}\n| extra19 = {{hlist|Tainy|Albert Hype}}\n| length19 = 4:00\n\n| title20 = <3\n| writer20 = {{hlist|Mart\u00ednez|Marco Masis|Melendez}}\n| extra20 = {{hlist|Tainy|Albert Hype}}\n| length20 = 2:37\n}}\n\n'''Sample credits'''\n* \"[[Si Veo a Tu Mam\u00e1]]\" contains interpolations from \"[[The Girl From Ipanema]]\", written by [[Ant\u00f4nio Carlos Jobim]], [[Vinicius de Moraes|Vin\u00edcius de Moraes]] and Norman Gimbel, performed by Stan Getz and Jo\u00e3o Gilberto.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/Bad-bunny-si-veo-a-tu-mama-lyrics|title=Si Veo a Tu Mam\u00e1|work=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last1=Fu|first1=Eddie|last2=Bell|first2=Javy|date=March 3, 2020|accessdate=March 3, 2020}}</ref>\n* \"La Santa\" contains interpolations from \"[[Aqu\u00ed Est\u00e1 Tu Caldo]]\", written and performed by Daddy Yankee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/9326471/bad-bunny-yhlqmdlg-essential-tracks|title=6 Essential Tracks on Bad Bunny's 'YHLQMDLG': Editors' Picks|work=Billboard|last1=Flores|first1=Griselda|last2=Roiz|first2=Jessica|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n* \"[[Vete]]\" contains interpolations from \"Si Te Vas\", written by Cesar Batista-Escalera, performed by Kartiel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/bad-bunny-vete-spanish-to-english-translation-samples-noriega-kartiers-si-te-vas|title=Bad Bunny Interpolates A Reggaeton Classic On \"Vete\"|work=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last1=Fu|first1=Eddie|last2=Bell|first2=Javy|date=November 21, 2019|accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref>\n* \"Ignorantes\" contains interpolations from \"No S\u00e9 Si Fue\", written and performed by Arc\u00e1ngel and [[Zion & Lennox|Zion]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.elmundo.es/f5/escucha/2020/02/18/5e4c10f421efa01d5b8b461f.html|title=Ignorantes, de Bad Bunny y Sech: letra y v\u00eddeo|work=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|language=Spanish|date=February 18, 2020|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|62|artist=Bad Bunny|album=YHLQMDLG|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Wallonia|75|artist=Bad Bunny|album=YHLQMDLG|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|17|M|url=https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2020/03/09/james-taylor-has-weeks-no-1-album|title=James Taylor Has This Week's No. 1 A